<item>
            <title>[SYNAPSE-902] Fault sequence gets invoked even when the responseAction of an endpoint timeout is set to discard.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-902</link>
                <project id="12310201" key="SYNAPSE">Synapse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Consider the following proxy service configuration. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;proxy name=&quot;TimeoutProxy&quot; transports=&quot;https http&quot; startOnLoad=&quot;true&quot; trace=&quot;disable&quot;&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;description/&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;target faultSequence=&quot;fault&quot;&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
         &amp;lt;endpoint&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;address uri=&quot;http://serverhost/TimeoutService/&quot;&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
               &amp;lt;timeout&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
                  &amp;lt;duration&amp;gt;1000&amp;lt;/duration&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
                  &amp;lt;responseAction&amp;gt;discard&amp;lt;/responseAction&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
               &amp;lt;/timeout&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;/address&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
         &amp;lt;/endpoint&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
         &amp;lt;outSequence&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;send/&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
         &amp;lt;/outSequence&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;/target&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/proxy&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The address endpoint is configured to discard the message if a timeout occurs. But it still invokes the fault sequence on a timeout. This is the same behavior of having &apos;fault&apos; as the &amp;lt;responseAction&amp;gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
